<h2>The Raspberry Pi - A Credit Card Sized Computer</h2>

<p>The Raspberry Pi is computer the size of a credit card. As well as being a compact computer it is also a very economical computer. The origional version was marketed as costing $35 (depending of course on your location).</p>
<p>All you need to get a Raspberry Pi up and running is a Secure Digital card (SD) and a copy of the (free) open source operating system. The download links can be found <a href="http://www.raspberrypi.org/downloads/">Here</a> </p> 



 </p>
<p>
<p>
